revisions:
[{'created': '2013-08-20 05:35:41.000000000', 'message': "Support for advanced service router

When creating an LR:
    - deploy an Edge asynchronously
    - create a L2 switch for connecting LR and Edge
    - attach a router port to the L2 switch.
    - assign ip address 169.254.2.1/28 and nexthop 169.254.2.3 to LR
When set external gateway:
    - configure Edge interface and default gateway
    - Add static routes to Edge for all logic networks attached to LR via nexthop 169.254.2.1
    - configure SNAT rules for all logic networks attached to LR
When add router interface:
    - Add static route/SNAT rule for the network attached to LR
When associate floating IP address:
    - configure DNAT rule for the floating ip and the port

Tests being done:
    - Verified Edge is deployed asynchronously and LR is attached to the internal created L2 switch
    - Manually attach Edge's vNic to the L2 switch and Edge is able to ping 169.254.2.1
    - Verified router-delete deletes Edge asynchronously and remove the internal L2 switch
    - Verified SNAT/DNAT/static-routes rules are configured on Edge in correct order
    - Verified external vnic ip address/netmask and default gateway is configured

TODO:
    - Attach Edge vNic to NVS network

Implements: blueprint nvp-service-router
Change-Id: If9eff53df4d65cf4e318dedbfaafc742f6c6ab7f

    - configure Edge interface and default gateway
    - Add static routes to Edge for all logic networks attached to LR via nexthop 169.254.2.1
    - configure SNAT rules for all logic networks attached to LR
When add router interface:
    - Add static route/SNAT rule for the network attached to LR
When associate floating IP address:
    - configure DNAT rule for the floating ip and the port

Tests being done:
    - Verified Edge is deployed asynchronously and LR is attached to the internal created L2 switch
    - Manually attach Edge's vNic to the L2 switch and Edge is able to ping 169.254.2.1
    - Verified router-delete deletes Edge asynchronously and remove the internal L2 switch
    - Verified SNAT/DNAT/static-routes rules are configured on Edge in correct order
    - Verified external vnic ip address/netmask and default gateway is configured

TODO:
    - Attach Edge vNic to NVS network

Implements: blueprint nvp-service-router
Change-Id: If9eff53df4d65cf4e318dedbfaafc742f6c6ab7f

commit_message:
Support for NVP advanced service router

When creating an LR:
    - deploy an Edge asynchronously
    - create a L2 switch for connecting LR and Edge
    - attach a router port to the L2 switch.
    - assign ip address 169.254.2.1/28 and nexthop 169.254.2.3 to LR
When set external gateway:
    - configure Edge interface and default gateway
    - Add static routes to Edge for all logic networks attached to LR via nexthop 169.254.2.1
    - configure SNAT rules for all logic networks attached to LR
When add router interface:
    - Add static route/SNAT rule for the network attached to LR
When associate floating IP address:
    - configure DNAT rule for the floating ip and the port

Tests being done:
    - Verified Edge is deployed asynchronously and LR is attached to the internal created L2 switch
    - Manually attach Edge's vNic to the L2 switch and Edge is able to ping 169.254.2.1
    - Verified router-delete deletes Edge asynchronously and remove the internal L2 switch
    - Verified SNAT/DNAT/static-routes rules are configured on Edge in correct order
    - Verified external vnic ip address/netmask and default gateway is configured

Implements: blueprint nvp-service-router
Change-Id: If9eff53df4d65cf4e318dedbfaafc742f6c6ab7f

subject: Ensure pid file is removed when metadata ns daemon receives SIGTERM
messages:
[{'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-09-10 09:42:06.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Works for me

Build succeeded.

- gate-neutron-pep8 http://logs.openstack.org/31/45831/1/check/gate-neutron-pep8/705e69d : SUCCESS in 2m 15s

- gate-neutron-python27 http://logs.openstack.org/31/45831/1/check/gate-neutron-python27/a6b7b2e : SUCCESS in 14m 06s

'}, {'account_id': 2592, 'date': '2013-09-10 12:24:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Looks good to me (core reviewer)

Good catch. Thank you for fixing this.'}, {'account_id': 1131, 'date': '2013-09-10 14:29:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

'}, {'account_id': 748, 'date': '2013-09-10 16:54:18.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

Nothing wrong with this fix per se, but is the user really supposed to send SIGTERM to neutron-ns-metadata-proxy and expect that everything worked normally? I wonder if a more appropriate fix would be to 'ignore' the signal and let the parent process handle the correct clean-up of the pidfile."}, {'account_id': 748, 'date': '2013-09-10 16:56:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: No score

meant no score'}, {'account_id': 2733, 'date': '2013-09-10 18:18:05.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

@Armando - yes, I think so. I'm thinking about when shutdown broadcasts SIGTERM - it just gives processes a chance to cleanup properly.

The parent process will be init. Do you mean the l3-agent or dhcp-agent that started the daemon? These agents don't actually stop the daemons when they themselves are stopped - I believe this is intended behaviour. All the daemon has to do is remove its pid file and I think the daemon itself is best placed to do that."}, {'account_id': 748, 'date': '2013-09-10 18:22:30.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Hi Darragh,

The parent process is init when the ns proxy is daemonized, which happens to be controlled by a config opt (daemonize is True by default). I wonder whether we'd need to do something different when the proxy is not daemonized, otherwise, the change looks good."}, {'account_id': 2733, 'date': '2013-09-11 07:45:31.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Hi Armando,

ok - I see what you mean - but I can't figure out how the daemonize option can be used. It is defined in namespace_proxy, which receives its options on the command line only. The only two clients that build the command line are l3_agent and dhcp_agent, and neither pass this option. I'm probably missing something here?

Thanks, Darragh."}, {'account_id': 2592, 'date': '2013-09-11 12:09:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

So the daemonize option is really used for command line testing.  When manually invoking the process, if daemonize=False the process will stay in the foreground.  We should not need any special handling for this case since a  pid file will not be written.'}, {'account_id': 748, 'date': '2013-09-11 16:41:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Looks good to me (core reviewer); Approved

Make sense. Thanks for clarifying my doubts.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-09-11 16:41:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: No score

[{'created': '2013-09-10 09:15:07.000000000', 'message': "Ensure pid file is removed when metadata ns daemon receives SIGTERM

These files from the metadata namespace proxy are not being removed
because delete_pid() is registered with atexit. This means it only runs
when a process exits normally and won't run when a process receives a
signal.

This patch registers a signal handler for SIGTERM that calls exit()
to make the process exit normally so delete_pid() gets called.

Fixes bug: 1223250

Change-Id: I6309802e2109359560ccc084559ec8e4d310cce2
"}]
commit_message:
Ensure pid file is removed when metadata ns daemon receives SIGTERM

These files from the metadata namespace proxy are not being removed
because delete_pid() is registered with atexit. This means it only runs
when a process exits normally and won't run when a process receives a
signal.

This patch registers a signal handler for SIGTERM that calls exit()
to make the process exit normally so delete_pid() gets called.

Fixes bug: 1223250

Change-Id: I6309802e2109359560ccc084559ec8e4d310cce2

commit_message:
Stack instance identifier property

The identifier property formats the stack name and ID for
REST API request paths.

This has the following consequences for each action method:
- get, same behaviour but using the identifier property
- delete, using the full identifier avoids one http redirect
- update, this method was non-functional before this change, and is
  now fixed

Change-Id: Ib2b12826243e25772acccb8ca56039e54d3857d5

_heal_instance_info_cache periodic task.  This will eliminate

commit_message:
Reduce DB load caused by heal instance info cache

Load system metadata with instance fetches in the
_heal_instance_info_cache periodic task.  This will eliminate
DB queries to lazy load the system metadata in _get_instance_nw_info.

(lazy loading happens in the Instance object's obj_load_attr method)

bug 1223969

Change-Id: I835fc73ef3a92885cec174e1533db10e28752fe1

commit_message:
Added button to Reboot multiple instances

Added a "Soft Reboot" button to reboot multiple instances from the project's
Instances panel, just like it is possible to Terminate multiple instances.

Change-Id: I61f61584888ebb61c835dadee9056f0657fa756e
Closes-Bug: #1213839

Previously deleting a key in certain qos specs was accomplished via
'update' API. Unfortunately, 'update' isn't able to tell the
difference between setting a key with no value and deleting a key (and
its value).
This change adds an new API 'delete_keys' to qos_specs API extension.
'delete_keys' API allows client to specify a list of to-be-deleted keys
in one single request (batch mode!), which can be handy when removing
multiple keys in a qos specs.

Example URL and request body for 'delete_keys' API:
 PUT to http://127.0.0.1:8776/v2/qos-specs/QOS_SPECS_UUID/delete_keys
 with body: {'keys': ['foo', 'bar', 'zoo']}

Above example request will result in 'foo', 'bar', 'zoo' key/value
pairs of QOS_SPECS_UUID be marked as deleted in DB.  If QOS_SPECS_UUID
doesn't exist, a 404 error will return; if any key in 'foo', 'bar',
'zoo' couldn't be found in QOS_SPECS_UUID, a 400 error will return with
error message telling which key couldn't be found. Note that Cinder
will puke 400 and stop trying the rest once it encounters a
non-existing (or deleted) key amoung the given list of keys.

This change also fixes 'show' API that used to include delted keys in
result.

Fix bug: # 1223660
Fix bug: #

commit_message:
Fix deleting qos specs key

Previously deleting a key in certain qos specs was accomplished via
'update' API. Unfortunately, 'update' isn't able to tell the
difference between setting a key with no value and deleting a key (and
its value).
This change adds an new API 'delete_keys' to qos_specs API extension.
'delete_keys' API allows client to specify a list of to-be-deleted keys
in one single request (batch mode!), which can be handy when removing
multiple keys in a qos specs.

Example URL and request body for 'delete_keys' API:
 PUT to http://127.0.0.1:8776/v2/qos-specs/QOS_SPECS_UUID/delete_keys
 with body: {'keys': ['foo', 'bar', 'zoo']}

Above example request will result in 'foo', 'bar', 'zoo' key/value
pairs of QOS_SPECS_UUID be marked as deleted in DB.  If QOS_SPECS_UUID
doesn't exist, a 404 error will return; if any key in 'foo', 'bar',
'zoo' couldn't be found in QOS_SPECS_UUID, a 400 error will return with
error message telling which key couldn't be found. Note that Cinder
will puke 400 and stop trying the rest once it encounters a
non-existing (or deleted) key amoung the given list of keys.

This change also fixes 'list'/'show' API includes deleted keys in
result.

Fix bug: # 1223660
Fix bug: # 1223677

Change-Id: Ia3cb07e204d655a9b837b317ce7117feb3c86a2d

commit_message:
Translate server extension attributes to json

Several server attributes looks different when using the xml
interface, because the namespace part appears in the attribute name.
This change translates 7 xml namespace attribute part to the json
equivalent.

Change-Id: Ie7a117207f0a1945964e1ca8c9d531c4af70211b

commit_message:
Don't return query from db API

The cell_update() method of the sqlalchemy db API returned a Query when
it really intended to return a Cell.  Fix this and tweak the db API test
so that it verifies that the result of this method is a Cell.

Change-Id: I7ab7ea19f00ac2e8c2c73afe8a14f331940b4580
Closes-bug: #1198796

commit_message:
Remove out of date list of jenkins jobs

The list of jobs in this doc file was out of date and most of the links
didn't work anymore.  Instead of trying to list out specifics which will
just get out of date again, include a generic pointer to where you can
find results (on code reviews).

Change-Id: Ief65281abae48bee6a679f76068e315227cf6991
Closes-bug: #1199577

commit_message:
Move novaclient to requirements.txt

novaclient is a runtime requirement in Havana both for volume
migration and qemu-assisted-snapshots.

Closes-Bug: #1223484
Change-Id: Ie7e8be2d0edf00cdb04f980a6aa247e04807bf67

commit_message:
fix missing unit in log message

Bad log message:
    "extend volume 1 to 2"
Correct one:
    "extend volume 1 GB to 2 GB"

(also update my profile in .mailmap)

Change-Id: I6d229c4440f2f5443b45a10f3912c20e21c63f32

commit_message:
libvirt: fix {attach,detach}_interface()

* The get_config() method now takes 6 arguments, instead of 5
  previously. This change has been introduced by commit 08f8773b.

* LibvirtConnTestCase: add the test_attach_interface_get_config() and
  test_detach_interface_get_config() methods to prevent future
  failures.

Fixes bug #1212565

(cherry picked from commit ff4863cca3012b2060bff788456c1b98b03d46d5)

Conflicts:
	nova/tests/test_libvirt.py
	nova/virt/libvirt/driver.py

Change-Id: I4e874f59595c3afe820103a27036519df1a126ff

commit_message:
Wrapping ssh calls into subprocesses

Eventlet does not work properly with Paramiko when several connections
are opened concurrently (see bug #1212341). The fix moves ssh calls
from main code to subprocess to avoid the issue.

Also changed:
 * added timeout to all remote operations
 * old SSH utilities were moved from remote.py to integration tests,
   because new ones can not be utilized there

Fixes: bug #1212341

Change-Id: Ib89af3a3bbcb587af46dad3431d512a21d1ba826

commit_message:

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-09-11 09:49:53.000000000', 'message': "Stop doing complex keystone intialisation.

Initialisation tasks which are one-time should be API orchestration
rather than instance level orchestration : doing otherwise makes
instance bring up a mass of special cases, and reduces flexability
below that that the base API offers. We're migration all things to
this pattern, keystone is merely the last in a line of fixes :).

Change-Id: I125a1c742289b3d1cf6319d127f4cf948459d9bc
"}]
commit_message:
Stop doing complex keystone intialisation.

Initialisation tasks which are one-time should be API orchestration
rather than instance level orchestration : doing otherwise makes
instance bring up a mass of special cases, and reduces flexability
below that that the base API offers. We're migration all things to
this pattern, keystone is merely the last in a line of fixes :).

Change-Id: I125a1c742289b3d1cf6319d127f4cf948459d9bc

does not exist on Fedora or RHEL.

user to connect to a system mode daemon, this configuration is necessary

commit_message:
Check libvirt connection URI

The libvirt connection URI should point to qemu:///system to allow the
user to connect to a system mode daemon, this configuration is necessary
for consistency, as some of the steps in TOCI assume that qemu:///system
is being used.

Change-Id: I19a2f03b1bdf7278175179824831e93987c2d54f

commit_message:
Bad parameters for setup-endpoints is an error.

Previously we would exit 0 if a bad option was supplied or too few/too
many arguments, which can lead to scripts failing to detect errors.

Change-Id: I3729b98ce959e8c310807daa4d51e0348229ea3f

commit_message:
Drop creation of demo tenant/user.

We inherited this from boilerplate in devstack/keystone docs. "demo"
is a user we should only create in demo clouds. As such this should
be directly under the users control, not hardcoded into the init
scripts.

Change-Id: I656ea00b2cb5666b27024d053a63c558fd9b6cb7

commit_message:
Initialise keystone itself via APIs

There is no need to initialize keystone on the initial machine (though
we should arrange for HTTP endpoints by default). Initializing via
APIs makes scale out with identical images easier to reason about.

Change-Id: Idf9d6ba17d6ef352d17f8bf593be970cca310321

commit_message:
Make having a demo user an explicit opt-in step.

There is no need for a demo user for under and seed clouds, so the
in-instance automation is about to drop that feature. API scripts
replace that code-path.

Change-Id: I9bbb4855d0b162c8e8d2dcfa778f92171279b3ff

commit_message:
Partial resolution to bug 121783

This change replaces RuntimeError exceptions in sqlalchemy/api.py
with NotFoundException which is derived from SavannaException. The
use of SavannaException will cause errors to be reported with more
detail through the REST api.

Change-Id: I570d5f4b0f07a3f0406180074e413a47cee51dd7
Implements: 121783

Despite looking awfully big, most of this patch just shuffles code around.
While this makes code analysis simpler, it still calls for a thorough testing which I will perform as soon as possible.

The discussion point so far are, in my opinion:

- split of agent scheduler in L2(DHCP) and L3 scheduler. This choice is consistent with the L2/L3 plugin split. The alternative design to consider is whether we should have a single agent extensions which is capable of dealing with both plugins, and switch off some operations in cases where the L3 one isn't available or does not support scheduling.

- creating a common base class/mixin for useful operations as _fields or _get_by_id

- Sort out (this might just be me not understanding how it works) the case in which prevent_l3_port_deletion is called by a L2 plugin which does not have the L3 functionality

- Extension naming and XML serialization. So far I think it's better to look at this problem than go ahead with improper and confusion ext aliases and try to sort this out later.

- Understand whether we should start running the separate L3 plugin for OVS, Linux Bridge, and other plugins by default. These plugins indeed do little to nothing in additions to what the db module does."}, {'account_id': 333, 'date': '2013-07-06 16:06:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: (2 inline comments)

as for separate_l3_plugin config variable to agent configuration.
Can it be deleted by negotiating between agent and server?
Quantum server (and plugin) provides configurations to agent and agent sets up based on those variable so that admin have to update only server config file.

Probably this idea would be extended to more generic framework and might be beyond this scope. And new BP would be required.'}, {'account_id': 2031, 'date': '2013-07-06 16:06:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(2 inline comments)

CI looks failing by this code.
I suspect we should update devstack for this patch first.
However code should be updated also ( I have commented inline)

But generally I'd consider a separate patch for such refactoring if there is a strict reason for it."}, {'account_id': 162, 'date': '2013-09-09 15:37:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 20: (6 inline comments)

The move of l3 db sheduling logic to a separate l3_agentschedulers_db.py is required because alchemy fails to create db tables properly otherwise. The failure happens for the case with a separate l3 routing service plugin. Since the core plugin is loaded before the service plugin the agentschedulers_db gets included with the core plugin. If the L3 scheduler db stuff is inside that file creation of the RouterL3AgentBindings table is attempted before the Routers table has been created (which happens when the L3 routing service plugin is loaded).'}, {'account_id': 162, 'date': '2013-09-09 15:38:08.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 21.'}, {'account_id': 162, 'date': '2013-09-09 15:46:41.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 22.'}, {'account_id': 2592, 'date': '2013-09-09 15:50:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 22: No score

commit_message:
Adds support for L3 routing/NAT as a service plugin

- Adds L3 routing/NAT service plugin
- Removes L3 routing/NAT from ML2 plugin
- Moves "router:external" attribute to new extension "External-net"
- Introduces separate RPC topic for L3 callbacks from L3 agent

Implements: blueprint quantum-l3-routing-plugin

Change-Id: Id9af10c2910f9a1730b163203a68d101ffc3b282

commit_message:
Fixed erroneous force full copy in ceph backup driver

The following steps should not result in a forced full copy:

1. create vol
2. create backup (works fine i.e. uses incremental diff)
3. delete backup
4. create new backup (full copy forced because volume backup-snap exists and is not ignored)

This patch resolves the above problem.

Change-Id: I61c245219f54f7ee942e06e343c5d79d4cab947b
Fixes: bug #1221836

commit_message:
Partial implement fake deploy engine

This engine is very usefull when we have already deployed OpenStack
cloud and would like to test it with Rally.

On deploy it just returns cloud config (endpoints users and so on)
that was specified in task config.

TODO: Add verification for input endpoints

blueprint deploy-engine-fake

Change-Id: I5c139f6b97312b6e4e00913c0a987f0bfbcb203f

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-08-14 08:53:36.000000000', 'message': 'NetApp NFS efficient clone_image impl.

This change implements clone_image funcionality
for NFS drivers. It implements an internal image cache
in nfs shares which will be used to clone images in case
the image_location supplied does not represent an nfs share
which could be used to directly clone image. It also implements
an internal cache cleaning mechanism at regular interval.

blueprint netapp-cinder-nfs-image-cloning

Change-Id: I20eaddf9febc78df33e31bd41b4698b772da3ae7
'}, {'created': '2013-08-14 11:26:56.000000000', 'message': 'NetApp NFS efficient clone_image impl.

This change implements clone_image funcionality
for NFS drivers. It implements an internal image cache
in nfs shares which will be used to clone images in case
the image_location supplied does not represent an nfs share
which could be used to directly clone image. It also implements
an internal cache cleaning mechanism at regular interval.

commit_message:
NetApp NFS efficient clone_image impl

This change implements clone_image funcionality
for NFS drivers. It implements an internal image cache
in nfs shares which will be used to clone images in case
the image_location supplied does not represent an nfs share
which could be used to directly clone image. It also implements
an internal cache cleaning mechanism at regular interval.

blueprint netapp-cinder-nfs-image-cloning

Change-Id: I20eaddf9febc78df33e31bd41b4698b772da3ae7

commit_message:
Register an extend_dict function for ext_gw_mode extension

Bug 1223585wq

Use dict extension methods instead of overriding make_router_dict in
order to make this extension consistent with all the others.

Change-Id: I94fa7e70e5a869963ec4dfa9de85c8d922976843

commit_message:
Rename rally.cmd.task_cli module to rally.cmd.main

It is not clear what it is "task_cli" and "main" is much better as
a name for the entry point.

Change-Id: I7fda8964e2d1f9d5e1a984bca234c5ad4ccdbf1a

commit_message:
Creating Alarm through API error

- fixing error of wrong parameters order when creating Alarm
  through API.
  Changing all parameters of Alarm __init__ to kwargs

Fixes bug 1223359

Change-Id: I9207ef17467bbcafb76ed9ea2743fd8596344b71

VPNaaS and FWaaS support in Horizon have been merged as FFE for Havana.
This commit updates the source lang PO files to sync Transifex resources.

PO files of other languages are not updated since they should be updated
by Transifex transifex.

commit_message:
Update the source languange PO files with FWaaS/VPNaaS support

VPNaaS and FWaaS support in Horizon have been merged as FFE for Havana.
This commit updates the source lang PO files to sync Transifex resources.

PO files of other languages are not updated since they should be updated
by Transifex transifex.

Change-Id: Ic2e93d6ec6e296e5e3c7e6c0e4731ce588f0d89d

commit_message:
Add check necessary parameter

"ceilometer alarm-create" and "ceilometer alarm-update" doesn't check
requirement parameters.

The following parameters are necessary parameters of "ceilometer
alarm-create".
* --name
* --counter-name
* --comparison-operator
* --threshold

The following parameters are necessary parameters of "ceilometer
alarm-update".
* --alarm-id

This patch fixes this problem.

Change-Id: Iabf67d5a9653c6c6f0926a46eecd6df3c4382863
Closes-Bug: #1223621

commit_message:
Create Auth Plugins

Create a V2 and a V3 auth plugin that are used to authenticate and
receive tokens. Provide deprecated handlers and proxying functions so
that we don't break any compatibility.

If an auth_plugin is not provided to the class then a base auth plugin
will be created to mimic the current behaviour.

This is as much as possible a refactoring, with the exception that
everything copied to the auth plugin is now private.

Part of: blueprint auth-plugins
Change-Id: Ieffda31213b965dd7fa1117a46474ece113bbbd0

commit_message:
Extract a base Session object

A wrapper around a number of connection variables. This will be extended
later with principals such as kerberos authentication and http sessions.

The intent is that this session object will become the basis for all
client based communication in OpenStack (as keystone wants to control
things like kerberos authentication).

Change-Id: I11449154cbd0bcc3bbfe54e8709d9eb669ccce2f
Part of: blueprint auth-plugins

commit_message:
Update invalid sql_connection error message

Previously, the sql_connection validation error
message had two problems:

1. It did not print out the offending string
2. The error was a bit misleading, b/c the
validation check does more than just check the
db_type.

This commit addresses the above issues in order
to ensure that users can better understand this
error message if they run into it.

Change-Id: Id5944bf035a13ad353d1417b13307067243a1a3c

Previously, the sql_connection validation error
message had two problems:

validation check does more than just check the
db_type.

to ensure that users can better understand this
error message if they run into it.

commit_message:
Add provides and requires properties to Flow

Provides and requires properties are used to browse all
required and provided values for the whole Flow.

The same properties were added to the Task.

Appropriate Task properties were renamed to rebind and save_as.

Change-Id: I02eb02303a9701a13f1a54f06f20bbf9aebd1d04

commit_message:
db.db_create() shouldn't call hiddenly db.db_drop()

It is nasty things that could produce a lot of problems.

Change-Id: I8a04c70817a9b975d6064693a2d27597c4b54d3e
